@node "histo" "History"

 History of Backclock
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

   V2.0:     Lots of bug fixed (first 'real' public version)
   V2.2:     CGX support (not functionnal !)
   V2.2ß3:   Bug fixed in CGX support (still not functioning !!!)
   V2.3:     Removed unused CGX code (supposed to work but not tested)
   V2.31:    Can deactivate the seconds arrow, problem when notify was not found
   V2.32b:   Now use rtracker.library (by me) to allocate and deallocate memory ...
   V2.32c:   Opens in front of Workbench or Directory Opus main window
             Last minute: It should work on CyberGFX now :)
                          Added a stay in front of WB window feature
   V3.00:    Use presets for clock shape
             Added a program for designing your own clock
   V3.1 :    Bugs removed in the Designer prog
             Length & position of the shadow can be changed
             Can use LEDs to display time
             Install script fixed (the guide icon was not copied)
             // RTracker now debugged (IMPORTANT bug fix)
   V3.21:    At last a commodity (!!!)
             Default public screen choosable
             And always some bug fix in Backclock & rtracker
   V3.22:    Just a little bugfix
@endnode

